remarks.format:
  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-102">帶狀線或階梯狀，會加上陰影的規則或自訂的間隔中的圖表背景的水平或垂直範圍。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-102">Strip lines, or strips, are horizontal or vertical ranges that shade the background of a chart in regular or custom intervals.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-103">您可以使用區域線：</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-103">You can use strip lines to:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1b855-104">改善可讀性，查閱在圖表上的個別值。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-104">Improve readability for looking up individual values on the chart.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1b855-105">在讀取圖表的個別資料點。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-105">Separate data points when reading the chart.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1b855-106">反白顯示定期出現，例如，若要識別週末資料點的日期。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-106">Highlight dates that occur at regular intervals, for example, to identify weekend data points.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1b855-107">反白顯示特定索引鍵範圍的資料。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-107">Highlight a specific key range of data.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1b855-108">加入臨界值線條在特定的常數值。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-108">Add a threshold line at a specific constant value.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-109">單一<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine>物件可以是繪製一次，或重複，在給定的間隔。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-109">A single <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine> object can either be drawn once, or repeatedly, for a given interval.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-110">這個動作由<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A>屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-110">This action is controlled by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-111">當-1 值指派給<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A>屬性、 一個寬帶繪製線條。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-111">When a value of -1 is assigned to the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property, one strip line will be drawn.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-112">當為非零的值指派給<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A>屬性，將會重複繪製帶狀線，在每個指定的間隔。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-112">When a non-zero value is assigned to the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property, a strip line will be drawn repeatedly at each given interval.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-113">繪製帶狀線的位置的位置也會受到<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffset%2A>和<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffsetType%2A>帶狀線的屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-113">The location where a strip line is drawn is also affected by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffset%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffsetType%2A> properties of the strip line.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-114">帶狀線一律會與相關聯<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.Axis>物件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-114">Strip lines are always associated with an <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.Axis> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-115">可以將它們加入的設計階段和執行的階段。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-115">They can be added at both design time and run time.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-116">若要加入的水平或垂直列顯示臨界值，設定<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A>0.0 的值的屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-116">To add a horizontal or vertical line to display a threshold, set the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> property to a value of 0.0.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-117">這會導致正在繪製一條線。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-117">This will result in a line being drawn.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-118">您可以使用<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A>，<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderDashStyle%2A>和<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderWidth%2A>色彩、 寬度和線條的樣式屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-118">You can use the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderDashStyle%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderWidth%2A> properties for the color, width and style of the line.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-119">沒有圖表背景屬性 (`Back*`) 時使用<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A>屬性設定為 0.0。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-119">No chart background properties (`Back*`) are used when the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> property is set to 0.0.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-120">使用<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Text%2A>帶狀線文字與帶狀線的屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-120">Use the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Text%2A> property of the strip line to associate text with a strip line.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-121">位置和方向，這段文字可以控制<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.TextAlignment%2A>屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-121">The placement and orientation of this text can be controlled by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.TextAlignment%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-122">針對相同的軸定義了多個區域線，很可能會重疊帶狀線。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-122">When multiple strip lines are defined for the same axis, it is possible that the strip lines will overlap.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-123">疊置順序的<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine>物件由其訂單中項目的<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLinesCollection>物件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-123">The Z-order of <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine> objects is determined by their order of occurrence in the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLinesCollection> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-124">這表示第一次出現的第一次; 繪製第二個會繪製為第二個，依此類推。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-124">This means that the first occurrence is drawn first; the second occurrence is drawn second, and so on.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-125">區域線不適用於下列圖表類型： 圓形圖、 環圈圖、 漏斗圖、 金字塔圖，Kagi、 ThreeLineBreak、 PointAndFigure、 極座標圖和雷達圖。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-125">Strip lines are not supported for the following chart types: Pie, Doughnut, Funnel, Pyramid, Kagi, ThreeLineBreak, PointAndFigure, Polar and Radar.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-126">下列程式碼範例示範三個應用程式的帶狀線。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-126">The following code example demonstrates three applications of strip lines.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-127">首先，水平帶狀線會新增週期性間隔。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-127">First, horizontal strip lines are added at recurring intervals.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-128">第二個、 垂直帶狀線會反白顯示週末資料點。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-128">Second, vertical strip lines are added to highlight weekend data points.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-129">最後，會加入非週期性帶狀線，表示圖表的第一個數列中資料點的平均值。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-129">Lastly, a non-recurring strip line is added to denote the mean of the data points in the first series of the chart.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Imports System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting  
  
Public Partial Class StripLines   
    Inherits System.Web.UI.Page   
    Protected Sub Page_Load(ByVal sender As Object, ByVal e As EventArgs)  
  
        ' Add chart data before adding strip lines.   
        AddChartData()   
  
        ' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.   
        AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
  
        ' Highlights weekend points using strip lines.   
        HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
  
        ' Adds a threshold line using strip lines.   
        AddThresholdStripLine()   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.   
    Private Sub AddChartData()   
        ' Declare new random variable   
        Dim rand As New Random()   
        For i As Integer = 0 To 6   
  
            ' Add a week of data   
            chart1.Series(0).Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.[Next](20, 35))   
        Next   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.   
    Private Sub AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
        ' Instantiate new strip line   
        Dim stripLine1 As New StripLine()  
        stripLine1.StripWidth = 2.5   
        stripLine1.Interval = 5   
  
        ' Consider adding transparency so that the strip lines are lighter   
        stripLine1.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Red)   
  
        ' Add the strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine1)   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds strip lines to highlight weekend values.   
    Private Sub HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
        ' Set strip line to highlight weekends   
        Dim stripLine2 As New StripLine()   
        stripLine2.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Gold)   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffset = -1.5   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffsetType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
        stripLine2.Interval = 1   
        stripLine2.IntervalType = DateTimeIntervalType.Weeks   
        stripLine2.StripWidth = 2   
        stripLine2.StripWidthType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.StripLines.Add(stripLine2)   
  
        ' Set the axis label to show the name of the day   
        ' This is done in order to demonstrate that weekends are highlighted   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.LabelStyle.Format = "ddd"   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds a horizontal threshold strip line at the mean value of the first series.  
    Private Sub AddThresholdStripLine()   
        Dim stripLine3 As New StripLine()   
  
        ' Set threshold line so that it is only shown once   
        stripLine3.Interval = 0   
  
        ' Set the threshold line to be drawn at the calculated mean of the first series   
        stripLine3.IntervalOffset = chart1.DataManipulator.Statistics.Mean(chart1.Series(0).Name)   
  
        stripLine3.BackColor = Color.DarkGreen   
        stripLine3.StripWidth = 0.25   
  
        ' Set text properties for the threshold line   
        stripLine3.Text = "Mean"   
        stripLine3.ForeColor = Color.Black   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine3)   
    End Sub   
End Class  
```  
  
```csharp  
public partial class StripLines : System.Web.UI.Page   
    {  
        protected void Page_Load(object sender, EventArgs e)  
        {              
            // Add chart data  
            AddChartData();  
  
            // Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.  
            AddHorizRepeatingStripLines();  
  
            // Highlights weekend points using strip lines.  
            HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines();  
  
            // Adds a threshold line using strip lines.  
            AddThresholdStripLine();  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddChartData()  
        {  
            // Declare new random variable  
            Random rand = new Random();  
  
            // Add a week of data  
            for (int i = 0; i < 7; i++)   
            {  
                chart1.Series[0].Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.Next(20,35));  
            }  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()  
        {  
            // Instantiate new strip line  
            StripLine stripLine1 = new StripLine();  
            stripLine1.StripWidth = 0;  
            stripLine1.BorderColor = Color.Black;  
            stripLine1.BorderWidth = 3;  
            stripLine1.Interval = 5;  
  
            // Consider adding transparency so that the strip lines are lighter  
            stripLine1.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Red);  
  
            stripLine1.BackSecondaryColor = Color.Black;  
            stripLine1.BackGradientStyle = GradientStyle.LeftRight;  
  
            // Add the strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine1);  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds strip lines to highlight weekend values.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()  
        {  
            // Set strip line to highlight weekends  
            StripLine stripLine2 = new StripLine();  
            stripLine2.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Gold);              
            stripLine2.IntervalOffset = -1.5;  
            stripLine2.IntervalOffsetType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days;  
            stripLine2.Interval = 1;  
            stripLine2.IntervalType = DateTimeIntervalType.Weeks;  
            stripLine2.StripWidth = 2;  
            stripLine2.StripWidthType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days;  
  
            // Add strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisX.StripLines.Add(stripLine2);  
  
            // Set the axis label to show the name of the day  
            // This is done in order to demonstrate that weekends are highlighted  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisX.LabelStyle.Format = "ddd";  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds a horizontal threshold strip line at the calculated mean   
        /// value of all data points in the first series of the chart.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddThresholdStripLine()  
        {  
            StripLine stripLine3 = new StripLine();  
  
            // Set threshold line so that it is only shown once  
            stripLine3.Interval = 0;  
  
            // Set the threshold line to be drawn at the calculated mean of the first series  
            stripLine3.IntervalOffset = chart1.DataManipulator.Statistics.Mean(chart1.Series[0].Name);  
  
            stripLine3.BackColor = Color.DarkGreen;  
            stripLine3.StripWidth = 0.25;  
  
            // Set text properties for the threshold line  
            stripLine3.Text = "Mean";  
            stripLine3.ForeColor = Color.Black;  
  
            // Add strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine3);  
        }  
    }  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-134">您可以為任何有效的 ARGB （alpha、 紅、 綠、 藍色） 值設定這個屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-134">You can set this property to any valid ARGB (alpha, red, green, blue) value.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-135">若要設定帶狀線的漸層，設定<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackColor%2A>和<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackSecondaryColor%2A>屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-135">To set a gradient for the strip line, set the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackColor%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackSecondaryColor%2A> properties.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-136">如果您設定此色彩為"透明"— 亦即，設定為 0 的 alpha 值-無色彩會指派給項目的背景。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-136">If you set this color to "transparent"—in other words, set the alpha value to 0—no color will be assigned to the background of the element.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-137">如此一來，背景會變成透明。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-137">As a result, the background will be transparent.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-138">如果<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A>屬性設定為 0.0 時，會繪製一條線和<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A>屬性會決定線條，不是這個屬性的色彩。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-138">If the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> property is set to 0.0, a line will be drawn and the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A> property will determine the color of the line, not this property.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-139">下列程式碼範例示範三個應用程式的帶狀線。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-139">The following code example demonstrates three applications of strip lines.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-140">首先，水平帶狀線會新增週期性間隔。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-140">First, horizontal strip lines are added at recurring intervals.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-141">第二個、 垂直帶狀線會反白顯示週末資料點。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-141">Second, vertical strip lines are added to highlight weekend data points.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-142">最後，會加入非週期性帶狀線，表示圖表的第一個數列中資料點的平均值。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-142">Lastly, a non-recurring strip line is added to denote the mean of the data points in the first series of the chart.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Imports System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting  
  
Public Partial Class StripLines   
    Inherits System.Web.UI.Page   
    Protected Sub Page_Load(ByVal sender As Object, ByVal e As EventArgs)  
  
        ' Add chart data before adding strip lines.   
        AddChartData()   
  
        ' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.   
        AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
  
        ' Highlights weekend points using strip lines.   
        HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
  
        ' Adds a threshold line using strip lines.   
        AddThresholdStripLine()   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub AddChartData()   
        ' Declare new random variable   
        Dim rand As New Random()   
        For i As Integer = 0 To 6   
  
            ' Add a week of data   
            chart1.Series(0).Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.[Next](20, 35))   
        Next   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
        ' Instantiate new strip line   
        Dim stripLine1 As New StripLine()   
        stripLine1.StripWidth = 2.5   
        stripLine1.Interval = 5   
  
        ' Consider adding transparency so that the strip lines are lighter   
        stripLine1.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Red)   
  
        ' Add the strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine1)   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds strip lines to highlight weekend values.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
        ' Set strip line to highlight weekends   
        Dim stripLine2 As New StripLine()   
        stripLine2.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Gold)   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffset = -1.5   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffsetType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
        stripLine2.Interval = 1   
        stripLine2.IntervalType = DateTimeIntervalType.Weeks   
        stripLine2.StripWidth = 2   
        stripLine2.StripWidthType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.StripLines.Add(stripLine2)   
  
        ' Set the axis label to show the name of the day   
        ' This is done in order to demonstrate that weekends are highlighted   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.LabelStyle.Format = "ddd"   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds a horizontal threshold strip line at the calculated mean   
    ''' value of all data points in the first series of the chart.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub AddThresholdStripLine()   
        Dim stripLine3 As New StripLine()   
  
        ' Set threshold line so that it is only shown once   
        stripLine3.Interval = 0   
  
        ' Set the threshold line to be drawn at the calculated mean of the first series   
        stripLine3.IntervalOffset = chart1.DataManipulator.Statistics.Mean(chart1.Series(0).Name)   
  
        stripLine3.BackColor = Color.DarkGreen   
        stripLine3.StripWidth = 0.25   
  
        ' Set text properties for the threshold line   
        stripLine3.Text = "Mean"   
        stripLine3.ForeColor = Color.Black   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine3)   
    End Sub   
End Class  
```  
  
```csharp  
public partial class StripLines : System.Web.UI.Page   
    {  
        protected void Page_Load(object sender, EventArgs e)  
        {              
            // Add chart data  
            AddChartData();  
  
            // Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.  
            AddHorizRepeatingStripLines();  
  
            // Highlights weekend points using strip lines.  
            HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines();  
  
            // Adds a threshold line using strip lines.  
            AddThresholdStripLine();  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddChartData()  
        {  
            // Declare new random variable  
            Random rand = new Random();  
  
            // Add a week of data  
            for (int i = 0; i < 7; i++)   
            {  
                chart1.Series[0].Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.Next(20,35));  
            }  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()  
        {  
            // Instantiate new strip line  
            StripLine stripLine1 = new StripLine();  
            stripLine1.StripWidth = 0;  
            stripLine1.BorderColor = Color.Black;  
            stripLine1.BorderWidth = 3;  
            stripLine1.Interval = 5;  
  
            // Consider adding transparency so that the strip lines are lighter  
            stripLine1.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Red);  
  
            stripLine1.BackSecondaryColor = Color.Black;  
            stripLine1.BackGradientStyle = GradientStyle.LeftRight;  
  
            // Add the strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine1);  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds strip lines to highlight weekend values.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()  
        {  
            // Set strip line to highlight weekends  
            StripLine stripLine2 = new StripLine();  
            stripLine2.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Gold);              
            stripLine2.IntervalOffset = -1.5;  
            stripLine2.IntervalOffsetType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days;  
            stripLine2.Interval = 1;  
            stripLine2.IntervalType = DateTimeIntervalType.Weeks;  
            stripLine2.StripWidth = 2;  
            stripLine2.StripWidthType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days;  
  
            // Add strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisX.StripLines.Add(stripLine2);  
  
            // Set the axis label to show the name of the day  
            // This is done in order to demonstrate that weekends are highlighted  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisX.LabelStyle.Format = "ddd";  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds a horizontal threshold strip line at the calculated mean   
        /// value of all data points in the first series of the chart.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddThresholdStripLine()  
        {  
            StripLine stripLine3 = new StripLine();  
  
            // Set threshold line so that it is only shown once  
            stripLine3.Interval = 0;  
  
            // Set the threshold line to be drawn at the calculated mean of the first series  
            stripLine3.IntervalOffset = chart1.DataManipulator.Statistics.Mean(chart1.Series[0].Name);  
  
            stripLine3.BackColor = Color.DarkGreen;  
            stripLine3.StripWidth = 0.25;  
  
            // Set text properties for the threshold line  
            stripLine3.Text = "Mean";  
            stripLine3.ForeColor = Color.Black;  
  
            // Add strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine3);  
        }  
    }  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-219">當您將<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A>屬性設為零 (0.0)，一條帶狀線的值將會顯示，且由指定寬度<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A>屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-219">When you set the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property to a value of zero (0.0), one strip line will be displayed, with a width specified by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-220">當您將<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A>將不會顯示值設為非零，多個帶狀線。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-220">When you set <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> to a value of other than zero, multiple strip lines will be shown.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-221">所使用的單位<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A>屬性由定義<xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalType%2A>屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-221">The unit that is used for the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property is defined by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalType%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="1b855-222">下列程式碼範例示範三個應用程式的帶狀線。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-222">The following code example demonstrates three applications of strip lines.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-223">首先，水平帶狀線會新增週期性間隔。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-223">First, horizontal strip lines are added at recurring intervals.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-224">第二個、 垂直帶狀線會反白顯示週末資料點。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-224">Second, vertical strip lines are added to highlight weekend data points.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1b855-225">最後，會加入非週期性帶狀線，表示圖表的第一個數列中資料點的平均值。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1b855-225">Lastly, a non-recurring strip line is added to denote the mean of the data points in the first series of the chart.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Imports System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting  
  
Public Partial Class StripLines   
    Inherits System.Web.UI.Page   
    Protected Sub Page_Load(ByVal sender As Object, ByVal e As EventArgs)  
  
        ' Add chart data before adding strip lines.   
        AddChartData()   
  
        ' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.   
        AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
  
        ' Highlights weekend points using strip lines.   
        HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
  
        ' Adds a threshold line using strip lines.   
        AddThresholdStripLine()   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub AddChartData()   
        ' Declare new random variable   
        Dim rand As New Random()   
        For i As Integer = 0 To 6   
  
            ' Add a week of data   
            chart1.Series(0).Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.[Next](20, 35))   
        Next   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
        ' Instantiate new strip line   
        Dim stripLine1 As New StripLine()   
        stripLine1.StripWidth = 2.5   
        stripLine1.Interval = 5   
  
        ' Consider adding transparency so that the strip lines are lighter   
        stripLine1.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Red)   
  
        ' Add the strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine1)   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds strip lines to highlight weekend values.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
        ' Set strip line to highlight weekends   
        Dim stripLine2 As New StripLine()   
        stripLine2.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Gold)   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffset = -1.5   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffsetType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
        stripLine2.Interval = 1   
        stripLine2.IntervalType = DateTimeIntervalType.Weeks   
        stripLine2.StripWidth = 2   
        stripLine2.StripWidthType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.StripLines.Add(stripLine2)   
  
        ' Set the axis label to show the name of the day   
        ' This is done in order to demonstrate that weekends are highlighted   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.LabelStyle.Format = "ddd"   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds a horizontal threshold strip line at the calculated mean   
    ''' value of all data points in the first series of the chart.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub AddThresholdStripLine()   
        Dim stripLine3 As New StripLine()   
  
        ' Set threshold line so that it is only shown once   
        stripLine3.Interval = 0   
  
        ' Set the threshold line to be drawn at the calculated mean of the first series   
        stripLine3.IntervalOffset = chart1.DataManipulator.Statistics.Mean(chart1.Series(0).Name)   
  
        stripLine3.BackColor = Color.DarkGreen   
        stripLine3.StripWidth = 0.25   
  
        ' Set text properties for the threshold line   
        stripLine3.Text = "Mean"   
        stripLine3.ForeColor = Color.Black   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine3)   
    End Sub   
End Class  
```  
  
```csharp  
public partial class StripLines : System.Web.UI.Page   
    {  
        protected void Page_Load(object sender, EventArgs e)  
        {              
            // Add chart data  
            AddChartData();  
  
            // Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.  
            AddHorizRepeatingStripLines();  
  
            // Highlights weekend points using strip lines.  
            HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines();  
  
            // Adds a threshold line using strip lines.  
            AddThresholdStripLine();  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddChartData()  
        {  
            // Declare new random variable  
            Random rand = new Random();  
  
            // Add a week of data  
            for (int i = 0; i < 7; i++)   
            {  
                chart1.Series[0].Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.Next(20,35));  
            }  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()  
        {  
            // Instantiate new strip line  
            StripLine stripLine1 = new StripLine();  
            stripLine1.StripWidth = 0;  
            stripLine1.BorderColor = Color.Black;  
            stripLine1.BorderWidth = 3;  
            stripLine1.Interval = 5;  
  
            // Consider adding transparency so that the strip lines are lighter  
            stripLine1.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Red);  
  
            stripLine1.BackSecondaryColor = Color.Black;  
            stripLine1.BackGradientStyle = GradientStyle.LeftRight;  
  
            // Add the strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine1);  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds strip lines to highlight weekend values.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()  
        {  
            // Set strip line to highlight weekends  
            StripLine stripLine2 = new StripLine();  
            stripLine2.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Gold);              
            stripLine2.IntervalOffset = -1.5;  
            stripLine2.IntervalOffsetType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days;  
            stripLine2.Interval = 1;  
            stripLine2.IntervalType = DateTimeIntervalType.Weeks;  
            stripLine2.StripWidth = 2;  
            stripLine2.StripWidthType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days;  
  
            // Add strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisX.StripLines.Add(stripLine2);  
  
            // Set the axis label to show the name of the day  
            // This is done in order to demonstrate that weekends are highlighted  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisX.LabelStyle.Format = "ddd";  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds a horizontal threshold strip line at the calculated mean   
        /// value of all data points in the first series of the chart.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddThresholdStripLine()  
        {  
            StripLine stripLine3 = new StripLine();  
  
            // Set threshold line so that it is only shown once  
            stripLine3.Interval = 0;  
  
            // Set the threshold line to be drawn at the calculated mean of the first series  
            stripLine3.IntervalOffset = chart1.DataManipulator.Statistics.Mean(chart1.Series[0].Name);  
  
            stripLine3.BackColor = Color.DarkGreen;  
            stripLine3.StripWidth = 0.25;  
  
            // Set text properties for the threshold line  
            stripLine3.Text = "Mean";  
            stripLine3.ForeColor = Color.Black;  
  
            // Add strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine3);  
        }  
    }  
